cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper analyzes a shared access network and studies the throughput and delay of the primary and secondary nodes. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates an optimization problem to maximize the throughput of the secondary network under delay constraints for the primary node, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a protocol to alleviate congestion at the primary node, which involves control systems concepts. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper assumes a system with multipacket reception (MPR) receivers, which is a common technique used in multimedia communication. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed protocol in terms of throughput and delay, which falls under the scope of performance evaluation.
